her variants?</h3>
<div itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"http://schema.o=
rg/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The <dfn>affine</dfn> ciphers in fact =
group together several ciphers which are special cases:</p>
<p>=E2=80=94 The <a href=3D"https://www.dcode.fr/multiplicative-cipher">mul=
tiplicative cipher</a> is a special case of the <dfn>Affine cipher</dfn> wh=
ere B is 0.</p>
<p>=E2=80=94 The <a href=3D"https://www.dcode.fr/caesar-cipher">Caesar ciph=
er</a> is a special case of the <dfn>Affine cipher</dfn> where A is 1 and B=
 is the shift/offest.</p>
<p>The <dfn>affine cipher</dfn> is itself a special case of the <a href=3D"=
https://www.dcode.fr/hill-cipher">Hill</a> cipher, which uses an <a href=3D=
"https://www.dcode.fr/matrix-inverse">invertible matrix</a>, rather than a =
straight-line equation, to generate the substitution alphabet.</p></div></d=
iv></div>
